1. Install the [BOSH v2 CLI](https://bosh.io/docs/cli-v2.html#install) on a machine outside of your PCF deployment. You can use the jumpbox for this task. 
1. From the Installation Dashboard in Ops Manager, select **BOSH Director > Status** and record the IP address listed for the Director.
You access the BOSH Director using this IP address.
  <img src="../images/director-ip.png"><br><br>
1. Click **Credentials** and record the Director credentials.
  <img src="../images/director-creds.png">
1. From the command line, log into the BOSH Director using the IP address and credentials that you recorded:
  <pre class='terminal'>
  $ bosh -e DIRECTOR_IP \
  --ca-cert PATH-TO-BOSH-SERVER-CERTIFICATE log-in
  Email (): director
  Password (): *******************
  Successfully authenticated with UAA
  Succeeded
  </pre>
